# Trivy false positives — investigated, not silenced blindly.
#
# CVE-2022-25235 / CVE-2022-25236 (expat, bundled in the "firefox"
# package): Trivy's Ubuntu OS-package DB tracks vulnerabilities for the
# distro's own "firefox" package. Since Ubuntu 22.04+, that package is a
# transitional stub that just installs the snap, versioned
# "1:1snap1-0ubuntu1" — the epoch (1:) makes it dpkg-compare as newer
# than ANY real Mozilla .deb build (ours is packages.mozilla.org,
# version scheme "<version>~buildN", no epoch), so Trivy always reports
# our real, up-to-date Firefox as vulnerable to these two 2022 CVEs.
# Documented, reproduced elsewhere: aquasecurity/trivy discussion #6792
# (https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/discussions/6792).
#
# Re-evaluate if Trivy changes how it resolves third-party .deb Firefox
# builds, or if these CVE IDs start showing up with a different
# (non-snap) fixed version.
CVE-2022-25235
CVE-2022-25236
